race.description: Midwest Gascoyne Volunteer Bush Fire Brigade Handicap
race.comment: YALLINGUP GIRL (7) led them up at this track and trip last time out and was too good, winning by 0.7L under Whittington, who remains in the saddle. Nicely placed under the conditions of this race, dropping in weight despite her strong figures last time out. Looks set to bring up back-to-back wins. MASTER ALEX (4) got a long way back his past couple but finished strongly most recently over 1407m, beaten just 1.9L. Back out to the mile may be his pet trip and the booking of Faithfull is a good push for his chances. Can land the knockout blow this time around. SOARING SOLO (3) faded when leading in BM70+ last time out and will find this a little easier. The blinkers come off now for Tsang who claims 3kgs. Has the speed to offset the tricky draw and can put her best foot forward.
